Full statement below on House Republicans' Unified Framework for Fixing our Broken Tax Code ↓

https://t.co/WYgzmgrX3j https://t.co/Rs8E2KjOgM
Americans needed a #taxreform plan long ago, which is why I reintroduced a business perspective on true tax reform called, #JumpstartAmerica https://t.co/mMVFXDLXdi
All this was great, but has likely been forgotten/replaced. While it’s important to remember our past, it’s crucial to improve our future
Lastly, President Reagan signed the Tax Reform Act of 1986 in to law
The Mets won the World Series
The world’s first disposable camera was invented
The Chicago Bears won the Super Bowl against the New England Patriots
Top Gun was the highest grossing film of the year with $8mil - the highest grossing film now is Beauty & the Beast, which made $504,017,165
The average cost of a new home in the U.S. was $104,100 - it is now $361,800
Pixar Animation Studios launched, and has since created 18 films
Mike Tyson won his first ever boxing title and became the youngest heavyweight champion in the world
The Oprah Winfrey Show aired for the first time
Let’s take a look back to remind ourselves why we should not be living with a tax plan that was created at the same time as the following:
Unfortunately, #taxreform didn't keep up w/ the times. It's outdated & our current plan is holding the US back from economic growth
It’s hard to believe 1986 was already 31 years ago. Some great things happened that year, but we’ve made some real progress since then…
It was humbling to watch these heroes be recognized for their bravery. Zack and I will forever be grateful for their valor on June 14, 2017
I had the great honor of congratulating Special Agents Crystal Griner & David Bailey on receiving the U.S. Capitol Policeman of Year Award https://t.co/EM6na7vuf5
ICYMI: https://t.co/nqDk4idp15
https://t.co/APAgEi2aBd
#JumpstartAmerica is smart and bold, and offers an authentic business perspective, which is exactly what this economy needs.
Full & Immediate Expensing: capital investment encourages economic growth & creates more jobs with higher wages
Inheritance Tax: the federal government should not punish those who pass their family business, or life savings onto their loved ones
Alternative Minimum Tax: repeal the AMT. This makes our current tax code even more complicated
The US must be a model for creating a competitive free market system – free of a tax code that discourages growth
Corporate Tax Rate: lowered to 20%. Lower taxes encourage economic growth & create good-paying jobs
Focus needs to be on relief for the lower and middle class, and creating economic opportunities for their future
Personal Tax Brackets: We need to simplify the code by reducing to three tax brackets
We need to jumpstart this economy. Here’s my plan → a business perspective on true #taxreform called, #JumpstartAmerica
It’s way past time for real change in Washington, and we need to give the American people real #taxreform
Americans are paying significantly too much and keep far too little of their hard earned dollars
